Elegant Retro Design

NOSTALGIC, ICONIC DESIGN: The Z fc's pentaprism design and body size, the black/silver-color elements, the circular eyepiece for the electronic viewfinder (EVF), and the design of the dials were all inspired by Nikon's legendary FM2 SLR film camera. - Quick, Smooth Autofocus: The Z fc supports Eye-Detection AF and Animal-Detection AF with the shooting of stills and video. The wide-area AF (L) AF-area mode is supported, ensuring the capture of eyes and faces by limiting the focusing area.

OPERATING DIALS: The top of Z fc's body features three dials and a small window that displays the aperture. The dials control shutter speed, exposure compensation and ISO sensitivity, allowing quick, efficient setting changes. Using the aperture display window, users are able to easily confirm and adjust the four basic settings for image-making at a glance. The i button and i menu support efficient shooting, by allowing quick adjustment of a variety of settings with the press of a button.

DEPENDABLE ISO RANGE: The capture of clear stills and videos in dark situations is made possible by covering a wide standard sensitivity range of ISO 100-51200. Additionally, shooting from high angles, as well as vertical shooting from low angles, is enabled with the adoption of the first vari-angle monitor among Z series cameras. When the monitor is rotated to the front, the camera automatically switches to self-portrait mode, providing smooth selfie shooting through touch operation.
details.product_descriptions: Blending classic looks with modern performance, the Nikon Z fc Mirrorless Digital Camera checks off all the boxes on a content creator's wish list: stylish and sleek retro design, impressive image quality with the Z mirrorless system flexibility, and it's optimized for vlogging and video applications. The Z fc is a DX-format mirrorless camera sporting a 20.9MP CMOS sensor, which pairs with EXPEED 6 image processing to realize quick shooting performance up to 11 fps, UHD 4K video recording at 30p, and sensitivity up to ISO 51200. Despite its classic looks, this camera is updated for contemporary content creation and features a fully articulating touchscreen LCD, supports live streaming, and has an advanced 209-point AF system with full-time subject tracking and eye-detection AF. The Z fc features several familiar physical controls on the body, including dedicated dials to adjust ISO, shutter speed, and exposure compensation. The body also features a 2.36m-dot OLED EVF and supports both Bluetooth, as well as SnapBridge wireless connectivity for pairing with a mobile device for remote camera control. Mixing a contemporary imaging approach with traditional form and function, the Nikon D780 is a versatile DSLR excelling in both photography and video applications. Featuring a 24.5MP full-frame CMOS sensor, high-resolution stills and video recording are possible, and the sensor features a BSI design for heightened clarity and reduced noise levels to suit working in a variety of lighting conditions.

This sensor also enables a wide sensitivity range from ISO 100-51200, which can be expanded to ISO 50-204800, along with a quick 7 fps shooting rate with the viewfinder or 12 fps in live view. This sensor also permits UHD 4K video recording up to 30 fps using either full-frame or cropped areas. Full HD recording up to 120 fps is available, too, along with integrated N-Log Gamma and HLG settings for refined color control.

Complementing the imaging, when working with the viewfinder, a 51-point phase-detection autofocus system is available, which includes 15 cross-type points for greater accuracy in low-light conditions. When working in live view or recording video, a 273-point Hybrid AF system is used that blends on-sensor phase-detection points and a contrast-detection system for quick performance and excellent subject tracking, including support for Eye-Detection AF.

details.product_descriptions: Magicue Studio 19″ Prompter with Pro Software Kit Overview The Magicue Studio 19″ Prompter with Pro Software Kit is a complete, modular teleprompting solution supporting a wide range of camera sizes. The prompter includes a 19″ LCD monitor offering HDMI, DVI, VGA, and Composite inputs and an HDMI output and downloadable prompting software. The prompter works with any standard size tripod supporting the required payload capacity. The downloadable PC/Mac compatible Magicue Pro software is suited for small studio setups and on-the-fly revisions. The modular design of the teleprompter allows for riser-less positioning, allowing the camera to remain stationery while letting the pad and hood unit be lowered into an optimal viewing position. A 60/40 beamsplitter glass clearly displays scrolling text from up to a 17 ft reading range. Assembly/disassembly is toolless and the system folds flat for convenient transport and storage.
